  "lyrics": "I'm down on my knees I'm wearing it on all of my knees I'm saying farewell to the rubble on my shoulders of responses I'm saying farewell for thinking that I can be Partnered up with someone eventually to see me for me But they never do, they only see the complicated robots I set in front of them Instead of personalizing it's just me, I'm just not the right way So with all this under me I say farewell to these thoughts of me I can't worry about your response to my needs I can't compromise me to make this moment last Cause if you want it, you want it, there's no way to say it Certain ways are nice, if you don't you just don't Let me move on, back to me Cause I need someone who knows me, someone who loves me, someone who doesn't Mad at my little bit of me I try to ask for So I say farewell to all the things that tell me not to be there for me And make it easier So I'm not gonna just be silent, I'm not just gonna die in obscurity Cause that wouldn't be fair to me So as you say goodbye to you that you lost inside of you And you say farewell to the thing that you thought was you I hope you feel all up on your knees The moment you know That it never comes back Thanks for watching!",
  "lyricsSegments": [
    {
      "end": 29.979999542236328,
